  "text": "Previous application of Systems biology and vaccinology approaches has resulted in the identification of genetic or immune signatures that correlate with vaccine efficacy for yellow fever [CITATION_1] , influenza [CITATION_2] and malaria [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . These predictive signatures can be used to identify novel mechanistic insights and aid the development of future vaccine strategies, while also serving as valuable biomarkers to screen for vaccine efficacy in future trials.",
